Bonjour à tous

Vous êtes étudiant en thèse ?

A summer school you could be interested in.  19-24 July 2021 Brasov, 
Romania. Free

Machine Learning for Earth Obversation and soft skills

School programme overview
Day 1: Earth Observation and Machine Learning – part I
Day 2: Earth Observation and Machine Learning – part II
Day 3: Open Science
Day 4: Soft Skills – part I
Day 5: Soft Skills – part II
Day 6: Career Development

Day-by-day school programme
Day 1 - Earth Observation and Machine Learning – part I
M. Ivanovici – Welcome speech and program presentation
F. Del Frate – Introduction to EO data
J. Mothe – Introduction to ML
R. Coliban – Visualization of hyperspectral images
J. Mothe, N. Neptune, M. Z. Ullah – Introduction to Deep Learning for EO 
– multispectral images (2h30 including a short break)
M. Datcu – Explainable AI for Earth Observation
M. Ivanovici – A fractal texture model for remotely-sensed hyperspectral 
images

Day 2 - Earth Observation and Machine Learning – part II
L. De Laurentiis, F. Del Frate – SAR images – Classification, object 
detection and other applications (2h30 including a short break)
A. Smeaton – Data augmentation and artificial training data
D. De Santis, F. Del Frate – Bio-geophysical parameter estimation with 
optical remote sensing (2h30 including a short break)
F. Del Frate – Open EO Education Resources and Initiatives
M. Ivanovici – Open Data. Open Science
L. F. Pau – Intellectual Property Rights
My PhD research work presented in 180 seconds
Career Aspirations (open discussion during social event; all)

Day 4 - Soft Skills – part I
D. Necșoi – Building successful teams (Part I: Foundations of team and 
teamwork: what are teams and why (and when) are they important?)
D. Necșoi – Building successful teams (Part II: How to build a team. The 
developmental stages of a team)
D. Necșoi – Building successful teams (Part III: Team effectiveness - 
principles for building an effective team/ team working skills)
D. Necșoi – Building successful teams (Part IV: Team processes: team 
decision making)

Day 5 - Soft Skills – part II
M. Voinea – Citizen in XXI-st century. How we develop the new social 
competences (debate)
M. Voinea – Citizen in XXI-st century. How we develop the new social 
competences (debriefing)
M. Voinea – Effective communication
M. Ivanovici – Research Project Management. Theory and practical aspects

Day 6 - Career Development
Meetings with stakeholders, teachers and coaches from industry

Interested: please email Josiane.Mothe@irit.fr



